Question: Describe winter season in your hometown (do not disclose the name of your hometown).
Answer:
Winter in my home town is cold, but there is barely any snow.  I think that perhaps everyone thinks that cold is what his or her hometown is like in the winter.  my home is in the south, so others may consider me to be a wimp.  but the trees lose their leaves and I have to wear coats, so I consider it winter.